# Go Package Installer

A simple Go binary used to install packages on Linux machines.

## Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**
    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/ashutosh5786/GO.git
    cd GO
    ```

2. **Build the binary:**
    ```bash
    go build -o installerx main.go
    ```

3. **Move the binary to a directory in your PATH:**
    ```bash
    sudo mv installer /usr/local/bin/
    ```

## Usage
### Install a Package

```bash
installerx <package-name>
```

## Upcoming Feature
### List Installed Packages

```bash
installerx list
```

### Remove a Package

```bash
installerx remove <package-name>
```